				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: OK not so noob to EQ but cannot figure out kiting... Retired BL<a name="37814"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 3 04 1:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll take a stab at this.
<br />

<br />
At your level you will have access to 2 really good AE dot songs:
<br />

<br />
Chords of Dissonance
<br />
http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=703&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=16
<br />

<br />
Denon's Disruptive Discord
<br />
http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=730&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=36
<br />

<br />
The next thing you will need is either sow potions or to keep your Selo's song running.  I would recommend sow potions since the speed at which you travel makes it easier to maintain.  Also you don't have to twist in Selo's so it makes the AE kite much much easier.  Also using Sow potions allow you to swap instruments in and out easily to up your AE songs power.  Make sure you keep track of the time and when your sow will be wearing off... it sucks to be in mid kite and your sow wears off but luckily for you Selo's will be your savior.
<br />

<br />
Level 28 from what I remember was a strange level because good hunting grounds dry up for AE kiting.  When you get to level 30 (?) is when you should start kiting snow cougars in Iceclad.
<br />

<br />
OK now how I did it.  Let's assume you get to level 30 and start doing snow cougars.  You can easily AE kite snow cougars up til around level 38-39.  Fastest experience for that level range.  Anyways... I click on my sow potion and then fire up Selo's for rounding up the cougars.  You have 2 islands to round them up.. just round up all you can see.  Start with 4-5 and work your way up as you get more and more comfortable.  Sow will outrun these snow cougars.  All you need to do is aggro these cougars by distance aggro or to run your train of snow cougars over another snow cougar.  Once you have a ton of cougars find a nice flat area and start running wide circles.  You can switch to different views (F9) to check on how the snow cougars are stacking up.  The trick is to start with wide circles to get them fairly close together then make your circles smaller and smaller.  Eventually all those cougars will appear to be just a couple cougars.  I once had like 15 cougars on my tail yet it looked like only 2.
<br />

<br />
Now comes the songs.  You should have one snow cougar targetted but if not target one of the cougars.  Use a stringed instrument and sing Chords of Dissonance.  As that lands swap out the instrument for brass instrument and sing Denon's Disruptive Discord.  Repeat.   Repeat... and keep on going.  
<br />

<br />
I would find sometimes that I would miss an entire song on all the cougars so what I tried to do was as the song was about to land I would turn.  I would end up running squares usually instead of circles cause I found that it was more efficient cause I was able to turn slightly into the pack of cougars and it would hit many of them.  Even if you have a pack of 15 and you only hit half you will soon make short work of them.  You might find that circles work really well for you... I just found squares worked well for me.
<br />

<br />
AE kiting has its drawbacks.  Dieing is one of those but simply bind yourself to the Soulbinder at the Iceclad docks and you will easily makeup any experience that you would lose from a rare death.  The snow cougars don't hit that hard but when you have 12-15 on your tail it adds up.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps.  I got through my 30's in just a few days.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
